8. TILEN.

You say my girl does nought but cry. Cry indeed she does, and the frequent tear rolls down her cheeks. But this is more pleasing than Aonian dew, as full of the sweet pathos of sad life. Know you not the pathetic nature of the Elegy, with its Pentameter subjoined to the Hexameter? Know you not what even the rough Thracians knew, folk who mourned when a child was

born? My little Muse shows precocious prevision as to the prelude of life's tune.
